Total War: WARHAMMER II - The Queen & The Crone (Main Menu)

 I was honored to work on Background image for Main Menu of Total...
caption:
Total War: WARHAMMER II - The Queen & The Crone (Main Menu)

I was honored to work on Background image for Main Menu of Total War: WARHAMMER II - The Queen & The Crone DLC. That artwork was later projected on 3d geometry and layers to create parallax and add FX (like snow and fire), by Creative Assembly team. I would like to give special thanks to Laurence Tully and David Lea for their help and guidance. Also I would like to thank https://www.artstation.com/telthona for tips and moral support .

summary: Drawing softwares for Mac Computer (any Mac)
body:
Drawing softwares for Mac Computer (any Mac)

Anybody know a good drawing software for Mac computers? I’ve been using medibang but drawing can be difficult and frustrating because when I stop using my tablet pen the pen brush keeps drawing anyways, when I draw it lags and I have to wait for it to draw, and when I want to draw something resembling a straight line it always looks like if I drew while my hand was trembling. I don’t know if it’s my Mac computer or medibang but I was wondering if any artist know what I can do. I’ve tried medibang and Tetsuya sketches so far and it’s still a bit frustrating to draw no matter what. I would use photoshop but my old photoshop won’t work on my computer and I heard that if I buy photoshop now it’s basically a monthly pay. I would appreciate it if anybody knows or uses any drawing software that it’s good for macs.

blog.name: autonomy1
blog.title: Peter Percival-AUTONOMY
blog.description: Shades, nuances, scraps of existence......looking directly at an object can sometimes be a meaningless, even a destructive use of time…in society we are trained to look at things quickly, process that information and move on to another view…so much information and meaning can be lost in the action of moving on….by changing the expected angle of view, or re-arranging elements of an image one can derive another meaning from it, and if not an absolute meaning an abstract one which makes us look once again…that is all one can ask for, another look…(©) Pete Percival - 2013 All Rights Reserved. Reproduction of any kind is illegal.

summary: Hello! I’m now open for Commissions! I never thought I would do this... but hey I need to help in my house to pay some bills,...
caption:
Hello! I’m now open for Commissions! I never thought I would do this… but hey I need to help in my house to pay some bills, sooooo commissions!!!

I am new with all of this so here’s how it works:

First you can email me at angela.mml801@gmail.com (<<that is also my paypal account where I only accept USD currency) or contact me here on tumblr. In this email/message you will need to include the following:

  • Your Email Address/Blog so that I may contact you.
  • What kind of commission you want? (example: Digital Half Body, Sketch Full Body, etc.)
  • How many characters are in this commission? (pricing varies as seen above, normally commission will be one character but if you want you can add more characters)
  • What type of background you want? it can be simple (flat unicolor, small elements like dots lines, etc. or none) or it can be detailed (like candies, food, flowers, sparkles, etc.) 
  • What is the mood of this piece? (happy? sad? scary? romantic?, etc.)
  • Send any additional pictures or reference
  • I will try to send you as soon as posible the sketches and then the inks, to look over for approval after some form of payment has been sent.
  • Notes: 
    • When you commission a “Traditional half/full draw” you can ask me if you desire for the original piece, so I will try to send it to you (Keep in mind this is an extra charge that you might want to pay, and it might varies depending of the region. I will let you know after the commission is done the extra charge you will need to pay for it)
    • “Sketch commission” would be in traditional, mainly because they give it a better effect of “sketchy look” also I have more control over what I am doing
    • For “Comic commission” I prefer you provide your own script (although I enjoy writing short stories, that takes a lot of time for me and that would slow down the process of all the commissions)

Other Information:

> After I approve your commission I will send you an invoice (Wait for the e-mail to show up and in it will be a link to pay me) so you can send the money via paypal and I will begin immediately. (It is also a more organized way to make sure you are paying for what you asked for.)

> I will post the commission online (Tumblr and/or Instagram). If you do not desire it to be shown to the world, you can always ask me and I’ll take note of it. (Your name or username is sufficient) 

> If the payment is canceled or the client withdraws while the commission is being worked on and if no reason is given why and the issue is not resolved, I will no longer continue working on the piece. (if this happened you have the right to ask for half of the refund)

I Will Draw: I can draw mostly anything you want, your ocs! that my little pony character, fursonas, animals, dragons, aliens, monsters! fan art!! even candy gore, cute lingerie, pin ups, maybe a robot, etc!

I Will Not Draw: Offensive, sensitive/racist material, same goes to political, gore, NSFW, excessive nudity, super detailed machinery, real life person (i can give it a try.. but I feel that my skill level aren’t that high so I don’t guarantee it will look good :´v )

(please note that I may refuse a commission if I am uncomfortable with the content so tell me the details of your commission!!!)

Thats all, thank you so much! ( ๑॔˃̶◡ ˂̶๑॓)

summary: I’M OPEN FOR COMMISSIONS AT A DISCOUNTED PRICE! I’m doing icons starting at $15, colored sketches at $25, and anything else...
caption:
I’M OPEN FOR COMMISSIONS AT A DISCOUNTED PRICE!

I’m doing icons starting at $15, colored sketches at $25, and anything else begins at $45. (the middle row of images are examples of each of these, respectively.) 

I have regularly priced commissions as well, and will absolutely take tips or donations. My Patreon is linked in the side bar, and you can ask me for mo Ko-fi page!

Things I’ll draw:

  • Fandom or Original content! Got a DnD/WoW char or an oc you want done?
  • Tasteful Gore or Nudity
  • Furry art
  • NSFW only if you have proof you are over 18 and even then, it’ll be very specific items only.

My hours have been cut again, and I’m beginning to realize how low I’m being paid at my day job, so I’d love to get my commissions back up and going again! If all you can do is reblog, that will go a long way toward helping me! Thank you <3

I’m doing icons starting at $15, colored sketches at $25, and anything else begins at $45. (the middle row of images are examples of each of these, respectively.) 

I have regularly priced commissions as well, and will absolutely take tips or donations. My Patreon is linked in the side bar, and you can ask me for mo Ko-fi page!

Things I’ll draw:

  • Fandom or Original content! Got a DnD/WoW char or an oc you want done?
  • Tasteful Gore or Nudity
  • Furry art
  • NSFW only if you have proof you are over 18 and even then, it’ll be very specific items only.

My hours have been cut again, and I’m beginning to realize how low I’m being paid at my day job, so I’d love to get my commissions back up and going again! If all you can do is reblog, that will go a long way toward helping me! Thank you <3
